            <Col id="rsltsurvey01">Additional questions based on the results</Col>
            <Col id="rsltsurvey02">Following questions are on whether your experiences on school violence have been resolved from the second semester of 2020 until now.</Col>
            <Col id="rsltsurvey03">Witnessing</Col>
            <Col id="rsltsurvey04">Have the following experiences of school violence been resolved?</Col>
            <Col id="rsltsurvey05">Experience of being a victim</Col>
            <Col id="rsltsurvey06">Verbal violence: I was cursed at, teased, and threatened with words.</Col>
            <Col id="rsltsurvey06_1">Verbal violence: I was cursed at, teased, and threatened with words.</Col>
            <Col id="rsltsurvey07">Coercion: I was forced to do something I didn't want to do because a friend, senior or junior made me do it.</Col>
            <Col id="rsltsurvey08">Taking money: My money or anything that is mine was taken away.</Col>
            <Col id="rsltsurvey09">Physical violence: I was beaten up by a friend, senior or junior, or got trapped inside a place.</Col>
            <Col id="rsltsurvey10">Sexual violence: I was sexually harassed, or abused.</Col>
            <Col id="rsltsurvey11">Cyberbullying: I was harassed in an online environment(Internet, smartphone, game console, etc.).</Col>
            <Col id="rsltsurvey12">Stalking: Even though I said I didn't like it, other students kept following me, harassing and making me anxious.</Col>
            <Col id="rsltsurvey13">Group Bullying: I was constantly bullied by friends, seniors and juniors.</Col>
            <Col id="rsltsurvey14">Has the school violence you witnessed been resolved?</Col>
            <Col id="rsltanswer01">It was resolved.</Col>
            <Col id="rsltanswer02">Not resolved yet.</Col>
            <Col id="rsltanswer03">I don't know.</Col>
            <Col id="rsltanswer04">Will you submit?</Col>
            <Col id="rsltanswer05">Would you like to save the draft?</Col>
            <Col id="tooltip06_1">[Example]I felt uneasy, because they cursed at me or made fun of my appearance.I felt uneasy and anxious, because they said something that scared me (e.g., Do you want to die).I felt uneasy, because they spread bad rumors about me.</Col>
            <Col id="tooltip06_2">[Example]I felt uneasy, because I was forced to do their homework or carry their bags and belongings instead.I felt uneasy, because I was forced to do errands.I felt uneasy, because they forced me to do something I hated to do.</Col>
            <Col id="tooltip06_3">[Example]I felt uneasy, because they took my money, personal items, and game items.I felt uneasy, because I didn't get my money, personal items, or game items back.</Col>
            <Col id="tooltip06_4">[Example]I was seriously injured by getting hit or knocked down.I felt uneasy, because I was trapped in a closed place such as a bathroom.I felt uneasy being pinched, hit, or pushed hard, which were disguised as a joke.</Col>
            <Col id="tooltip06_5">[Example]I felt uneasy, because I was forced to see erotic pictures or videos even though I said I didn't like it.I felt uneasy, because they didn’t stop talking and acting offensively even though I said I didn't like it.I felt uneasy, because they kept groping and touching my body even though I said I didn't like it.</Col>
            <Col id="tooltip06_6">[Example]I felt uneasy, because there were severe cursing towards me, teasing about my appearance in chats or on online posts.I felt uneasy, because bad rumors about me spread on online posts or social media.I felt uneasy and I was scared, because others said something that scared me through text messages (e.g., Do you want to die).</Col>
            <Col id="tooltip06_7">[Example]I felt uneasy, because someone kept following me or calling me, even though I said I didn't want to meet.I felt uneasy, because someone kept lying on the internet or on social media, saying that I was his/her boyfriend or girlfriend even though I said I didn't like it</Col>
            <Col id="tooltip06_8">[Example]I felt uneasy, because other students prevented me from hanging out with my friends, seniors and juniors.I felt uneasy, because other students didn’t answer me and kept ignoring me, even when I talked to them.I felt uneasy, because other students kept avoiding me on purpose.</Col>
            <Col id="tooltip16_1">[Example]I swore or made fun of another student’s appearance.I scared and threatened another student (e.g.,  Do you want to die).I spread bad rumors about another student.</Col>
            <Col id="tooltip16_2">[Example]I forced another student to do homework or to carry a bag in my stead.I forced another student to do errands.I forced another student to do something he/she hated to do.</Col>
            <Col id="tooltip16_3">[Example]&lt;/p&gt;I stole money, belongings, or game items from another student.After borrowing money, goods, or game items from other students, I did not return them.</Col>
            <Col id="tooltip16_4">[Example]I badly hurt another student by hitting or knocking them down on purpose.I locked up another student in a closed space, such as a bathroom.I harassed another student by pinching, beating, and pushing while disguising it as a joke.</Col>
            <Col id="tooltip16_5">[Example]Even though other students said they didn't like it, I showed them erotic pictures or videos.Even though other students said they didn't like it, I continued to talk and act sexually.I groped or touched others’ bodies even when they said they didn't like it.</Col>
            <Col id="tooltip16_6">[Example]I made fun of other students' appearances and cursed at them in a chat or on online posts.I made bad rumors about other students on online posts or social media.I scared other students (e.g., Do you want to die).</Col>
            <Col id="tooltip16_7">[Example]Even though other students said they didn't want to meet, I kept following or calling.I kept lying on the Internet or on social media and told others that he/she was my boyfriend or girlfriend, even though they told me they didn't like it.</Col>
            <Col id="tooltip16_8">[Example]I prevented other students from getting along with their friends, seniors and juniors on purpose.Even when a particular student talked, I did not answer and kept ignoring them.I kept avoiding a particular student.</Col>
            <Col id="tooltipTit">See Expanation</Col>
            <Col id="tooltipTitIns">Example(s)</Col>
            <Col id="tooltip37_1">[Self-Resolution by Heads of Schools]&lt;br&gt;If all four following requirements are met,  </Col>
            <Col id="tooltip37_2">it is a system that allows schools to resolve issues on their own with the consent of the victims and parents.</Col>
            <Col id="tooltip37_3">Where a medical report certifying that at least two weeks are needed for physical or mental treatment has not been issued</Col>
            <Col id="tooltip37_4">Where there is no property damage or damage has been immediately recovered</Col>
            <Col id="tooltip37_5">Where the school violence is not persistent</Col>
            <Col id="tooltip37_6">Where it is not a retaliatory action against a report, statement, provision of data, etc. on the previous school violence.</Col>
